# Pew dbt high-risk areas

Extends [safe-change-review](safe-change-review.mdc). Applies to Pew Digital Data Mart (`ddm-dbt`).

## High-risk areas

- `sitecore_item_id` filters and grain
- `unique_key` on `fct_content_*` / `mart_content_*`
- `user_pseudo_id` casts in GA4 raw
- Traffic source normalization (`fct_content_sources_daily`)
- Facebook metric bridge (quarterly KPI doc)
- GA4 seed backfills — scope is date/incident specific

## Pew consumer specifics

When checking the [consumer checklist](safe-change-review.mdc#consumer-checklist):

3. **Civis jobs** — `pewdigital/civis-dbt` image; confirm selectors, tags, model names
4. **Looker Studio** — exposure YAML and dashboard fields
6. **Docs** — [`docs/metrics/`](../../docs/metrics/), [`docs/CHANNEL_QUARTERLY_KPI_METRICS.md`](../../docs/CHANNEL_QUARTERLY_KPI_METRICS.md) for channel metrics

